# 1989 Emperor's Cup final

'''1989 Emperor's Cup Final''' was the 69th final of the Emperor's Cup competition. The final was played at National Stadium in Tokyo on January 1, 1990. Nissan Motors won the championship.
Overview
Defending champion Nissan Motors won their 4th title, by defeating Yamaha Motors 3â€“2. Nissan Motors was featured a squad consisting of Shigetatsu Matsunaga, Tetsuji Hashiratani, Kazushi Kimura, Nobutoshi Kaneda and Takashi Mizunuma.
